<H2>Why is GuildMagic running slowly or giving occasional errors when I use a form page?</H2>
<P>
Quite simply we need more bandwidth.
<P>
GuildMagic is WAY more popular that we expected. That's fantasic - we're thrilled - but in order to keep the site running smoothly we've had to keep upping the server specs and bandwidth. As you'd expect that's meant a rise in our hosting costs too.
<P>
<H2>Do I get anything special for donating?</H2>
<P>
How about our undying gratitude? :-)
<P>
Ok, how about this.. Any person donating more than $30 gets to advertise the guild of their choice on the GuildMagic home page with a graphical button linked to the guild's stat's and info page for 1 month. You'll need to supply me with a 120x32 image. Alternatively you could use your free 1 month ad to advertise anything you like (as long as it's legal, and suitable for a PG13 audience!). Just email your graphic image with an explanation of which paypal donation it relates to to <A HREF="mailto:lus@otn.co.uk">lus@otn.co.uk</A>
<P>
<H2>Why don't you charge people to use GuildMagic?</H2>
<P>
GuildMagic is provided free of charge. We believe this is important because a system like this is only useful if as many people as possible sign up and use it. 
<P>
<H2>What about advertising?</H2>
<P>
Advertising just doesn't pay for a site like GuildMagic any more. The bottom has dropped out of the internet advertising market. We hate pop-up ads as much as you do and we're trying hard to avoid using them to generate income. Pop-ups do still generate some income, though so we've not totally ruled that option out yet.
<P>
<H2>How can I help?</H2>
<P>
You can help by making a voluntary contribution towards the hosting costs for the web site. We don't expect everyone will contribute. In fact we have no idea how many will - we've never done anything like this before - so we don't know how much to ask for. Go with your conscience.
<P>
<H2>What does it cost to provide GuildMagic?</H2>
<P>
We don't expect to give up our jobs on the income from GuildMagic. Sure that would be nice but we're realistic. We'll just be happy if the site pays for its own internet costs. At the moment we pay over $1000 per year for our hosting. That's an absolute bargain price - thanks <A HREF="http://www.ntidesign.com/">NTI Design</A>, you guys ROCK. In the first 6 months we've had $499.44 of donations through paypal. With the advertising income it looks like we're on target to pay for our hosting for the year but donations have tailed off significantly recently - we need people to keep contributing!
<P>
<H2>What is PayPal?</H2>
<P>
PayPal is a really easy, secure way to send money to someone. It's the same system Allakhazam is using and it's also incredibly popular with e-bay users. You sign up with their system, tell them about your bank account and from then on you can send money to people and pay for stuff with just an email address and a password. Find out more <A HREF="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_home" TARGET="_blank">here</A> or click the PayPal button above to sign up and then send us your donation. Better still - if you quote "john@otn.co.uk" as the person that referred you when you sign-up with Paypal then we get a $5 bonus!
